Nodecaf Changelog

[BC]: Breaking Change
[NF]: New Functionality
[BF]: Bug Fix

2019-06-13 [v0.5.3]
- [BF] Fixed code generation error standard
- Changed code generation to use spaces instead of tabs
- Added missing default message for REST errors thrown from assertions
- Added regression test cases for a few bugs fixed on previous releases

2019-06-12 [v0.5.2]
- [BF] Fixed user error handler not being executed when headers were already sent
- Added missing default message for REST errors thrown as strings
- Added missing options for conf file generation with cli init
- [BF] Fixed undefined server name being shown when terminating from command line

2019-06-11 [v0.5.1]
- Updated ci to paralelize the lengthy code quality job
- Added log warning when an error happens after the response haders have been sent
- [BF] Fixed undefined app name field being shown when running from command line
- Moved logger code to own file
- [NF] Logger now serializes 'req' key as a node request object
- [BF] Fixed undefined error on subsequent close calls
- Fixed some space/tabs on README.md

2019-06-10 [v0.5.0]
- [BC] Renamed the whole project.
- Updated gitlab ci to use a pre-built mocha/nyc docker image for testing
- [BC] Moved from Restify to Express for the internal route server
- Changed conf file generation to create parent directories if needed
- Fixed server to correctly await start and close events
- [NF] Added path field to request log entry

2019-06-02 [v0.4.1]
- [NF] Added setting to log all incoming requests
- [NF] Added logging capabilities through bunyan package

2019-06-01 [v0.4.0]
- [NF] Improve terminal signal and uncaught exception handling
- [NF] Add capability for assertion module to be used on event callbacks
- [BC] Rewritten error handling code for better interface consistency
- [NF] Added cli command to generate the basic file structure for nodecaf projects
- Rearranged files necessary for test cases to a common directory

2019-05-29 [v0.3.0]
- Fixed deprecated equality assertions on test suite
- [BF] Fixed conf loader to not output warning when no conf path is provided
- [BF] Fixed exception when route errors would trigger an error event without listeners
- [BF][BC] Fixed default error handler that would attach itself again on every request

2019-05-27 [v0.2.0]
- [NF] Added an Assertions module to handle common REST exception scenarios.
- [BC] Improved error handling to always produce a valid REST output.
- Added test case for multipart and file support.

2019-05-17 [v0.0.1]
- First officially published version.
